# PhotoToSheet — Project Context

## Product
PhotoToSheet extracts structured data from photos and PDFs (receipts, invoices, W-2s, etc.) into CSV/JSON. Live at **https://phototosheet.com**. Operated by Datalytics LLC, Denver, CO. Contact: hello@phototosheet.com.

## Hosting & Deployment
- **Vercel** — deploys from `main` branch on GitHub (`alex-douglas/photo-spreadsheet`)
- Environment variables must be set in Vercel dashboard (not just `.env.local`)
- Pushing to `main` triggers production deployment
- **Vercel Analytics** enabled (cookie-free, no banner needed)

## Key Integrations

### Supabase (database)
- Tables: `device_wallets`, `email_wallets`, `credit_grants`, `upload_events`
- Credits system: 1 credit = 1 image scan or 1 PDF page
- New visitors get 1 free credit (per device, rate-limited by IP)
- Email wallets are the primary wallet after linking; device wallets are ephemeral
- Admin client in `lib/supabase/admin.ts`, credit logic in `lib/credits-server.ts`
- `upload_events` logs anonymous usage (doc type, mime, pages, cost) — no PII

### Stripe (payments)
- Using **Stripe Elements** with PaymentIntents (not Checkout redirect) — users pay inline
- Single product "Page Credit" (prod_UH1HaZkClfSx8Y), price ID in `STRIPE_PRICE_ID` env var
- $0.25/credit, preset packs (10/25/60) plus custom amounts (5–500)
- Credit granting is idempotent via `credit_grants` table (keyed on `payment_intent_id`)
- Webhook at `/api/stripe/webhook` for `payment_intent.succeeded` (backup grant)
- `/api/stripe/confirm-payment` for instant grant after client-side payment success
- Env vars: `NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`, `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY`, `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET`, `STRIPE_PRICE_ID`

### Google Gemini (AI extraction)
- Used for document classification and field extraction
- Multi-page PDFs are split into single-page PDFs via `pdf-lib` before sending to Gemini
- Extraction prompts in `lib/extraction-prompts.ts`

